@barcoboy Thank you for the detailed feedback — you're right, the previous fix did not handle the interactive login case.

**Root cause:** When no credentials are stored, PuTTY shows a login prompt. Our fix waited for the terminal title to change (signaling auth completion), but included a timeout fallback that still sent the opening command after `MaxPuttyWaitTime` (default: 2 seconds) — right into the username/password prompt.

**New fix:** When the timeout fires and the title has NOT changed,...
